Example 3:

Input: root = []
Output: []

Approach:If the current node is NULL, return NULL.
Swap the left and right child of the node.
Recursively invert the left subtree.
Recursively invert the right subtree.
Return the root.
The entire tree gets mirrored.

Algorithm:
Create a recursive function invertTree(root).
If root == NULL, return NULL.
Swap root->left and root->right.
Call invertTree(root->left).
Call invertTree(root->right).
Return root.

Complexity
Time: O(n) (visit every node once)
Space: O(h) (recursive call stack, where h is the tree height)
Best case (balanced tree): O(log n)
Worst case (skewed tree): O(n)

class Solution {
public:
    TreeNode* invertTree(TreeNode* root) {
        if (root == NULL)
         return NULL;

        swap(root->left, root->right);

        invertTree(root->left);
        invertTree(root->right);

         return root;
    }
};
